description:
&quot;Tabletop Simulator is the only simulator where you can let your aggression out by flipping the table! There are no rules to follow: just you, a physics sandbox, and your friends. Make your own games and play how YOU want! Unlimited gaming possibilities!&quot;

FAQ
Q: Does the multiplayer work in this version?
A: As of now (09.11.2014), v3.2 is the latest version, therefore you can connect to anyone with this version. Even when this version becomes outdated, you can host a server and play with friends, as long as you have the same version. If you're unsure what version you have, look at the bottom left corner in the main menu. This one says, &quot;Early Access v3.2&quot;. To the right you can see the latest version. As of now, it says, &quot;Latest version: 3.2&quot;.

To change your in-game name, open LumaEmu.ini.
You'd better change it right after you install the game, because some people would ban you on their servers just because you have the default name (and you're a pirate).

You'd better play this game with friends, because most people who host games have a password on them.

View changelog.txt.

